The management agreed to follow the following recommended measures to improve operations, viz:
1. Conduct extensive and strategic planning for 20% DF projects by formulating project proposals only after a feasibility study, detailed engineering, location survey and the like. Also, proposed projects shall be accompanied by POWs which is a result of thorough analysis of budget estimates. Early submission of proposals and POWs is also recommended;
2. Include in the Municipality’s Project Procurement plan (PPMP) and Annual Procurement plans each project that involves procurement process, with due consideration to the prescribed procurement activity timelines;
3. Ensure securing ownership over the land to be used for infrastructure projects. Negotiations for donation or acquisition of lot need to be done prior to the timelines set for project implementation to preclude delays due to ownership disputes; and
4. Direct the Municipal Project Monitoring Team to conduct proper periodic monitoring and submit progress reports to ensure that planned development projects are implemented and delivered promptly and efficiently.

