1. The audit team recommended the overall assessment and evaluation of Municipal Treasury’s collection system against the prescribed procedures in the Local Treasury Operations Manual, existing rules and regulations and best practices in treasury operations. Also, the responsible municipal officials will endeavor to strengthen the internal control procedures over cash and continuously monitor its operating effectiveness.
Specifically, the team recommended and the management agreed that:
2. Collector who are assigned in the Office of the Municipal Treasurer or within the proximity of the said office shall remit their collection to the liquidating officer at the close of the business day; in the case of collectors assigned in the field, where travel time form their places of assignment to the Local Treasury Office is more than one (1) day, turnover of collections shall be made at least once a week or as soon as the collections reached P5,000.00; the liquidating officer remit the same to the Municipal Treasurer for deposit to the AGDB; and properly accomplished RCDs shall be prepared in all stages;
3. Following the LTOM, only one RPT Receipt shall be issued for the collection of RPT, both basic and SEF counterpart so as to properly account for the accountable forms and also to ensure the simultaneous deposit of the said collection. The municipal treasurer shall deposit separately to the accounts of General Fund and Special Education Fund, respectively;
4. Only one stub of accountable forms shall be issued at a time to the collectors. No subsequent issuance shall be made unless the previously issued accountable forms have been liquidated to ensure that they are fully and properly accounted for. Also, prepare and submit monthly the Report of Accountability of Accountable Forms to monitor the issuance and liquidation of all accountable forms; and
5. Immediately reconcile issued and liquidated accountable forms for each collector by comparing the list of all issued accountable forms and all RCDs to determine if there are accountable forms which are not yet presented for liquidation and demand them from the collectors.

